Subject: RE: [VB] Cant get Tie Rod off

... by gosh and by golly, its off!!!!!!

I went down to the local parts store and a 'pickle fork' for $7.00.
Both sides of the bad tie rod wouldnt come off at first.  The one in the
center came off quickly after sticking the fork in and a couple of good
tugs.

The one on the wheel was a bit more difficult.  Since the one on the center
was off I could spin the wheel.  I cut it full left, stuck the pickle fork
where the end of the handle was sticking on the outside of the vehicle.  I
then jumped on the pickle fork handle and it came off <g>

Time to relace the steering dampner (since I am there and put everything
back together.

Thanks everybody!!!!!
--Rich


